================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1953
S.P. 761 In Senate, May 7, 2025
Protections from Liability to Landowners
(AFTER DEADLINE)
Approved for introduction by a majority of the Legislative Council pursuant to Joint Rule

Section 2:
205.
Reference to the Committee on Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry suggested and
ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BRENNER of Cumberland.
Cosponsored by Representative DUCHARME of Madison and
Senators: BLACK of Franklin, CARNEY of Cumberland, FARRIN of Somerset,
HARRINGTON of York, Representatives: DILL of Old Town, WOODSOME of Waterboro.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 14 MRSA §159-A, sub-§4, ¶B, as amended by PL 1995, c. 566, §1, is
3 further amended by amending subparagraph (1) to read:
4 (1) The landowner or the landowner's agent by the State; or
5 Sec. 2. 14 MRSA §159-A, sub-§4, ¶B, as amended by PL 1995, c. 566, §1, is
6 amended by enacting a new subparagraph (3) to read:
7 (3) The landowner or grantor who grants, and the holder or grantee who accepts,
8 an easement or other legal instrument that makes an express grant of perpetual
9 public access over premises for the public to pursue recreational or harvesting
10 activities; or
11 Sec. 3. 14 MRSA §159-A, sub-§7 is enacted to read:
12 7. Perpetual grant of public access. A landowner or other grantor who grants, and a
13 holder or grantee who accepts, an easement or other legal instrument that includes a
14 perpetual right of public access over premises for the public to pursue any recreational or
15 harvesting activities, in reliance on the protections from liability established by this section
16 as they exist at the time of the grant, as evidenced by an instrument recorded in the registry
17 of deeds for the county in which the premises are located, acquires a permanent vested
18 property right to those protections for any rights so granted, which runs to their heirs,
19 successors and assigns.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This bill provides additional protection from liability for a landowner or other grantor
2222 who grants, and a holder or grantee who accepts, an easement or other legal instrument that
2233 includes or makes an express grant of perpetual public access over premises for the public
2244 to pursue recreational or harvesting activities.
